00:15:44.520 --> 00:15:49.050
OK, so I'm going to begin by
solving some linear equations.

00:15:49.050 --> 00:15:50.190
Those are linear--

00:15:50.190 --> 00:15:54.210
I'm now speaking to family and--

00:15:54.210 --> 00:15:58.680
but speaking to you
all, just only the class

00:15:58.680 --> 00:16:01.290
certainly will know this.

00:16:01.290 --> 00:16:04.680
So that's three equations.

00:16:04.680 --> 00:16:08.040
And there are three
unknowns, x, y, and z,

00:16:08.040 --> 00:16:12.210
and the goal is to find those
three numbers, x, y, and z.

00:16:12.210 --> 00:16:15.300
So this is maybe the
most standard problem

00:16:15.300 --> 00:16:18.030
in linear algebra--

00:16:18.030 --> 00:16:20.520
n equations and n unknowns.

00:16:20.520 --> 00:16:23.070
In this example, n equals 3.

00:16:23.070 --> 00:16:25.530
So how do we proceed?

00:16:25.530 --> 00:16:27.960
How do we find x, y, and z?

00:16:27.960 --> 00:16:33.990
Well, the idea comes thousands
of years ago in China,

00:16:33.990 --> 00:16:37.680
and the key word is elimination.

00:16:37.680 --> 00:16:40.890
We don't any 0's there.

00:16:40.890 --> 00:16:47.280
It's 0's that make
calculations easier.

00:16:47.280 --> 00:16:51.240
And so let me show you how--

00:16:51.240 --> 00:16:51.945
the steps.

00:16:51.945 --> 00:16:57.240


00:16:57.240 --> 00:17:00.420
For those who know it well--
so the first equation,

00:17:00.420 --> 00:17:02.460
I won't change--

00:17:02.460 --> 00:17:08.670
2x plus 3y plus 4z equal 19.

00:17:08.670 --> 00:17:11.500


00:17:11.500 --> 00:17:13.598
What I want to get
is some 0's here.

00:17:13.598 --> 00:17:17.409
I want the second
equation to start with 0.

00:17:17.410 --> 00:17:19.210
So how do I do--

00:17:19.210 --> 00:17:22.690
where I now have
a 4, I want a 0.

00:17:22.690 --> 00:17:25.190
So I have that equation set.

00:17:25.190 --> 00:17:28.870
And I subtract 2 times that
equation from this one.

00:17:28.870 --> 00:17:34.660
I choose that number, 2, so
the 2 times 2x will be 4x.

00:17:34.660 --> 00:17:37.030
And when I subtract,
I'll have a 0.

00:17:37.030 --> 00:17:39.580
So that, I multiply that by 2.

00:17:39.580 --> 00:17:43.280
So 2 times 3y is 6y, leaving 5y.

00:17:43.280 --> 00:17:46.170


00:17:46.170 --> 00:17:53.520
And 2 times 4z is 8z
from 14, leaving 60.

00:17:53.520 --> 00:17:59.200
And 2 times 19 is 38
from 55, leaving 17.

00:17:59.200 --> 00:17:59.970
OK.

00:17:59.970 --> 00:18:02.730
So we've got an
easier equation now,

00:18:02.730 --> 00:18:05.280
and I'll do the same
for the third equation.

00:18:05.280 --> 00:18:08.910
This time, I have a 2x
there and a 2x there,

00:18:08.910 --> 00:18:12.750
so I just want to subtract
that equation from this one

00:18:12.750 --> 00:18:21.460
to make this 0x plus 3y
taken away from 8y leaves 5y.

00:18:21.460 --> 00:18:26.440
And 4z from 17z is 13z.

00:18:26.440 --> 00:18:30.640
And 19 from 50 is 31.

00:18:30.640 --> 00:18:34.310
OK, so we've taken
the first step.

00:18:34.310 --> 00:18:40.130
We've got 0's in the first
column below the pivot,

00:18:40.130 --> 00:18:44.590
the number that we
used to get those 0's.

00:18:44.590 --> 00:18:51.330
OK, so I'm partway along, and
then the idea is to continue.

00:18:51.330 --> 00:18:59.870
And I now look at the
second and third equations.

00:18:59.870 --> 00:19:03.890
I have two equations here,
and they just involve y and z.

00:19:03.890 --> 00:19:05.340
So I'm making progress.

00:19:05.340 --> 00:19:07.950
I had three equations
with three unknowns.

00:19:07.950 --> 00:19:10.730
Now I have two equations
with two unknowns.

00:19:10.730 --> 00:19:16.370
And let's go to one
equation with one unknown.

00:19:16.370 --> 00:19:21.170
So I want to get
a 0 there, right,

00:19:21.170 --> 00:19:24.840
so that I'll just have
z's and a right-hand side.

00:19:24.840 --> 00:19:28.220
So if I subtract,
everybody sees--

00:19:28.220 --> 00:19:30.380
is sort of getting in the swim.

00:19:30.380 --> 00:19:36.440
If I subtract that equation from
this one, it'll be 0x 0y and--

00:19:36.440 --> 00:19:37.280
what is it?

00:19:37.280 --> 00:19:45.160
7z equal 17 from 31 is 14.

00:19:45.160 --> 00:19:48.110
OK, so now I have--

00:19:48.110 --> 00:19:55.970
and so now I have an equation
for z all alone and equation

00:19:55.970 --> 00:20:01.460
for y and z together and the
starting equation for x, y,

00:20:01.460 --> 00:20:02.940
and z all together.

00:20:02.940 --> 00:20:04.520
So what's next?

00:20:04.520 --> 00:20:06.110
Go backwards.

00:20:06.110 --> 00:20:11.420
Solve this equation for z
then back to this one for y

00:20:11.420 --> 00:20:13.940
and then back to this one for x.

00:20:13.940 --> 00:20:22.130
So this is called elimination,
and it was invented in China

00:20:22.130 --> 00:20:24.240
3 or 4,000 years ago.

00:20:24.240 --> 00:20:25.440
So I'm sorry.

00:20:25.440 --> 00:20:28.700
This is a little
bit old mathematics,

00:20:28.700 --> 00:20:33.170
but it's the basic
step that simplifies,

00:20:33.170 --> 00:20:36.180
and then I'll show
you a little more.

00:20:36.180 --> 00:20:38.930
So let's go backwards.

00:20:38.930 --> 00:20:41.900
Maybe you could all
do it as I do it.

00:20:41.900 --> 00:20:48.330
If we solve that equation for
z, I get z equal to 2, right?

00:20:48.330 --> 00:20:54.370
Divide by 7, and now if z
is 2, then 13z here is 26.

00:20:54.370 --> 00:20:58.160
So I have 5y and 26 and 31.

00:20:58.160 --> 00:21:01.110
Well, if I subtract
the 26 from the 31,

00:21:01.110 --> 00:21:05.620
I'm moving the 26 over with
31 because it's just a number.

00:21:05.620 --> 00:21:09.600
So I'm subtracting
this 26 leaves

00:21:09.600 --> 00:21:13.530
me 5, so I have 5y equal 5.

00:21:13.530 --> 00:21:18.720
So 5y equal 5 is what that
equation has become, and told

00:21:18.720 --> 00:21:21.370
me that y is 1.

00:21:21.370 --> 00:21:27.730
And finally, I come
back to the top equation

00:21:27.730 --> 00:21:30.220
because I now know y and z.

00:21:30.220 --> 00:21:34.000
So if z is 2, that's 8.

00:21:34.000 --> 00:21:36.760
If y is 1, that's 3.

00:21:36.760 --> 00:21:40.720
So I have 3 and 8
and 19 there, so I

00:21:40.720 --> 00:21:42.430
should be able to figure out x.

00:21:42.430 --> 00:21:45.520


00:21:45.520 --> 00:21:47.650
Do you see what x is?

00:21:47.650 --> 00:21:50.380
Yeah, let me-- this
is for the class, now.

00:21:50.380 --> 00:21:53.380
I got you this far
by elimination.

00:21:53.380 --> 00:21:57.310
So I have this equation
to solve for x,

00:21:57.310 --> 00:21:58.540
and then I've got the answer.

00:21:58.540 --> 00:22:02.320
I've got all of x, y, and z.

00:22:02.320 --> 00:22:03.820
So what do I have?

00:22:03.820 --> 00:22:06.310
The 4z is 8.

00:22:06.310 --> 00:22:08.560
3y, this is 3.

00:22:08.560 --> 00:22:10.135
And 2x is what?

00:22:10.135 --> 00:22:12.670


00:22:12.670 --> 00:22:13.170
AUDIENCE: 8.

00:22:13.170 --> 00:22:13.410
AUDIENCE: 8.

00:22:13.410 --> 00:22:14.410
GILBERT STRANG: 2x is 8?

00:22:14.410 --> 00:22:15.570
Thanks.

00:22:15.570 --> 00:22:19.180
Professors need help,
especially at this point.

00:22:19.180 --> 00:22:21.460
2x is 8, so x is--

00:22:21.460 --> 00:22:21.960
AUDIENCE: 4.

00:22:21.960 --> 00:22:23.460
GILBERT STRANG: 4, Well done.

00:22:23.460 --> 00:22:27.300
100%, A for the whole class.

00:22:27.300 --> 00:22:29.810
[CHEERING, APPLAUSE]

00:22:29.810 --> 00:22:33.010
OK, right.

00:22:33.010 --> 00:22:34.450
OK.

00:22:34.450 --> 00:22:40.450
So let me just say that,
if we were doing this

00:22:40.450 --> 00:22:45.550
on the computer,
we wouldn't keep

00:22:45.550 --> 00:22:48.460
repeating all these
letters, x and y and z,

00:22:48.460 --> 00:22:51.910
and all the plus signs
and all the equal signs.

00:22:51.910 --> 00:22:54.100
I would write those equations--

00:22:54.100 --> 00:22:57.460
or the original equations,
I would write as--

00:22:57.460 --> 00:23:00.090
oh dear, that's out of sight.

00:23:00.090 --> 00:23:02.500
OK.

00:23:02.500 --> 00:23:04.690
So I would write the
original equations

00:23:04.690 --> 00:23:18.350
as 2, 3, and 4, 4, 11,
and 14, 2, 8, and 17.

00:23:18.350 --> 00:23:21.490
So that's the--
there is the matrix,

00:23:21.490 --> 00:23:26.440
the matrix of coefficients, the
matrix of the right-hand side--

00:23:26.440 --> 00:23:28.570
of the numbers on
the right-hand side.

00:23:28.570 --> 00:23:34.570
And they multiply if we define
multiplication suitably.

00:23:34.570 --> 00:23:37.600
There, there's the
x, y, z unknown.

